description:
From January 11 until prospectively Feb. 14, contact restrictions in Hesse (Germnay) are tightened. In public spaces, members of a household may only meet with one other person. Children also count towards this limit. There are exceptions for joint childcare of up to three families or for the accompaniment and care of minors or persons in need of support. Previously, meetings of relatives from two households, but no more than five people, were allowed. Children up to 14 years of age were not considered. Exeptions are made for public transport, 
for escorting and caring for minors or persons in need of assistance,
for the taking of certain examinations, for meetings of persons who must work together directly for business, professional, official or care-related reasons, for research and teaching at universities, vocational and music academies and non-university research institutions, 
in the context of mutual assumption of child care by a maximum of three families (family care community),
for meetings and court hearings and in cases where it is necessary to go below the minimum distance in order to ensure the operation of the meeting
